raw_data.title: Agile/Kanban Coach
raw_data.description: The Agile/Kanban Coach works with the team or organization to establish and adapt to Agile/Kanban practices that help to ensure high quality results and a high level of customer satisfaction.  The Agile/Kanban Coach is responsible for the ensuring that the Agile development practices are followed and adjusted as required. Specifically, the coach is responsible for Facilitation of meetings and reviews, and helping leaders, teams, departments and/or organizations are progressing forward on the path of continuous improvement.  The coach helps facilitate important recurring processes such as work replenishment, daily standup, deployment planning, risk reviews, service delivery, operations, and strategic planning.  The coach helps ensure that key metrics such as lead time, throughput, and work in progress are maintained and reviewed on a regular basis to facilitate decision-making.  The coach encourages regular reflection and review to identify and implement improvements along with a means to determine their efficacy.  The Coach may train one or more “apprentice” within an organization in order to transition the necessary knowledge needed to continue progress and to ensure that improvements are institutionalized and maintained over time.
